Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery vessel, seven lines of black-painted demotic text survive on the interior, the exterior is covered with a light-brown slip and faint traces of a further eight lines of black-painted Greek text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393890) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393890)
